The game was given moderate reviews, resulting in the [[Metacritic]] score of 65. Namco Bandai posted on its fiscal year report that the game sold 420,000 copies across all platforms in the US and Europe.<ref>{{cite web | author=Alexander, Leigh | date=August 4, 2009 | title=Namco Bandai Sees Loss As Afro Samurai Tops Sales | url=http://gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=24704 | work=Gamasutra.com | accessdate=2009-08-04}}</ref>
==Sequel== An episodic sequel was announced in June 2015, called ''[[Afro Samurai 2: Revenge of Kuma]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Afro Samurai 2: Revenge of Kuma story trailer sets the stage for revenge|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/12/8774549/afro-samurai-2-revenge-of-kuma-story-trailer-sets-the-stage-for|last=Campbell|first=Colin|date=June 12, 2015|accessdate=July 1, 2015}}</ref> Volume 1 was released on [[PlayStation 4]], and [[Microsoft Windows|PC]] on September 22, 2015 and the [[Xbox One]] on October 8, 2015. In November 2015, the game was removed from the [[PlayStation Store]], [[Xbox Marketplace]] and [[Steam (software)|Steam]] and volumes 2 and 3 were cancelled due to poor reception.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Biordi|first1=Jordan|title=Versus Evil Explains the Disappearance of Afro Samurai 2|url=http://www.cgmagonline.com/articles/news/versus-evil-exafro-samurai-2/|website=Comics Gaming Magazine|accessdate=20 November 2015|date=19 November 2015}}</ref>
