[[File:C.L. Wagner (LOC).jpg|thumb|Wagner in 1916]] '''Charles Ludwig Wagner'''(1869 - February 25, 1956) was a [[concert impresario]]. He managed [[John McCormack (tenor)|John McCormack]] and [[Mary Garden]] and introduced [[Walter Gieseking]].<ref>{{cite news |author= |title=Charles Wagner, Impresario, Dies. Concert Manager Who Made Fortune With McCormack, Sponsored Mary Garden, Sponsored Coloratura, Introduced Gieseking |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1956/02/26/archives/charles-wagner-impresario-dies-concert-manager-who-made-fortune.html |newspaper=[[New York Times]] |date=February 26, 1956 |accessdate=2015-01-20 }}</ref>
==Biography== He was born in 1869. He died on February 25, 1956 at [[Roosevelt Hospital]] in Manhattan.
